  "output": "## Test coverage: crawler app\n\n**Current state: 0%.** No `tests/` directory, no test files anywhere in `apps/crawler` (only `.venv`'s own pytest package and claude-flow's own log noise turned up). `pytest` is already a declared dev dependency in `pyproject.toml`, so the tooling is in place but unused.\n\nModules in scope: `base.py` (`NewsSource` + free functions), `providers.py` (11 provider subclasses, 3 with custom crawl logic), `main.py` (CLI), `models.py` (pure dataclasses — no behavior, skip).\n\n---\n\n### 1. `base.py` — free functions\n\n| Function | Untested branches / edge cases |\n|---|---|\n| `_fetch_xml` | gzip-magic-byte sniff (`\\x1f\\x8b`) vs plain XML; leading-newline strip (Midi quirk); non-UTF8 bytes (`errors=\"replace\"`) |\n| `discover_sitemap_urls` | sitemapindex recursion vs flat urlset; nested `<image:image><image:loc>` must NOT be picked up (only direct `<loc>` children); empty `<loc>` text ignored |\n| `parse_french_date` | `\"D Month YYYY\"` vs `\"Month D, YYYY\"`; accented months (`février`, `août`, `décembre`) vs unaccented (`fevrier`); unknown month → `None`; no match → `None` |\n| `parse_numeric_date` | valid `DD/MM/YYYY`; trailing time ignored; no match → `None`; **no validation of invalid calendar values** (e.g. `32/13/2024` — will raise `ValueError` uncaught, not tested) |\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base_functions.py\nimport pytest\nfrom base import _fetch_xml, discover_sitemap_urls, parse_french_date, parse_numeric_date\n\nclass TestFetchXml:\n    def test_decompresses_gzip_by_magic_bytes(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...  # mock urlopen to return gzip'd bytes, assert decompressed str returned\n\n    def test_strips_leading_whitespace_before_xml_decl(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...  # response body starts with \"\\n<?xml ...\"\n\n    def test_replaces_invalid_utf8_bytes(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...  # response body has invalid utf-8 sequence, assert no raise\n\n\nclass TestDiscoverSitemapUrls:\n    def test_flat_urlset_yields_locs(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...\n\n    def test_sitemapindex_recurses_into_children(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...\n\n    def test_ignores_nested_image_loc(self, monkeypatch):\n        # <url><loc>a</loc><image:image><image:loc>b</image:loc></image:image></url>\n        # only \"a\" should be yielded\n        ...\n\n\nclass TestParseFrenchDate:\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n        (\"22 juin 2019\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n        (\"octobre 30, 2017\", \"2017-10-30\"),\n        (\"15 février 2020\", \"2020-02-15\"),\n        (\"15 fevrier 2020\", \"2020-02-15\"),\n        (\"not a date\", None),\n        (\"32 juin 2019\", None),  # currently would raise, not return None — bug candidate\n    ])\n    def test_parse(self, text, expected):\n        assert parse_french_date(text) == expected\n\n\nclass TestParseNumericDate:\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n        (\"22/06/2019\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n        (\"22/06/2019 14:30\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n        (\"no date here\", None),\n    ])\n    def test_parse(self, text, expected):\n        assert parse_numeric_date(text) == expected\n\n    def test_invalid_calendar_date_raises(self):\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n            parse_numeric_date(\"32/13/2024\")\n```\n\n**Bug-shaped gap worth flagging**: `parse_french_date`/`parse_numeric_date` construct `datetime(...)` directly from regex-captured ints with no range validation — an out-of-range day/month raises `ValueError` instead of returning `None` like the \"no match\" path does. Since these run inside `parse_article()`, which is only wrapped by `crawl()`'s per-article `try/except`, this degrades to \"skip article\" rather than crashing — but it's inconsistent behavior worth a test either confirming or fixing.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `base.py` — `NewsSource`\n\n| Method | Gaps |\n|---|---|\n| `_load_state` / `_save_state` | missing state file → default `{\"seen_urls\": [], \"total_saved\": 0}`; **corrupted JSON in state file is untested and unhandled** (`json.loads` will raise, uncaught anywhere in `crawl()`); atomic write (tmp file + `.replace`) not verified |\n| `_append_article` | JSONL append format, `ensure_ascii=False` (non-ASCII Malagasy/French text) not verified |\n| `fetch` | `needs_stealth` branch (StealthyFetcher vs Fetcher) never exercised |\n| `parse_article` | title-missing → `None`; body paragraph filtering (empty `<p>` dropped); `published_date_attr` vs text+format branches; `embed_url` iframe found vs `about:blank` skipped vs falls back to `<video><source>`; no selectors matching anything |\n| `_extract_images` | dedup across cover_image + body imgs; `data-src` preferred over `src`; `data:` URIs skipped; relative→absolute via `urljoin` |\n| `crawl` | **the core state machine — entirely untested**: skip already-seen URLs; per-article exception → logged + skipped, not fatal; `article is None` → marked seen, `total_saved` NOT incremented, state saved; `limit<=0` unlimited; `limit` reached → early return + `last_stopped_reason`; exhausted → `last_stopped_reason`; **exception raised by `list_article_urls()` itself is caught and does not propagate** (only comment claims this — no test asserts it); `on_save` callback fired only for actually-saved articles |\n\n```python\n# tests/test_news_source_crawl.py\nimport pytest\nfrom base import NewsSource\nfrom models import Article, SiteSelectors\n\nclass FakeSource(NewsSource):\n    source_name = \"fake\"\n    selectors = SiteSelectors(title=\"h1\", body=\"p\")\n\n    def __init__(self, urls, articles_by_url=None, fail_urls=None, discovery_error=None):\n        self._urls = urls\n        self._articles_by_url = articles_by_url or {}\n        self._fail_urls = fail_urls or set()\n        self._discovery_error = discovery_error\n\n    def list_article_urls(self):\n        if self._discovery_error:\n            raise self._discovery_error\n        yield from self._urls\n\n    def parse_article(self, url):\n        if url in self._fail_urls:\n            raise RuntimeError(\"boom\")\n        return self._articles_by_url.get(url)\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef isolated_dirs(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"base.STATE_DIR\", tmp_path / \"state\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"base.LOG_DIR\", tmp_path / \"logs\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"base.DATA_DIR\", tmp_path / \"data\")\n    return tmp_path\n\n\ndef make_article(url):\n    return Article(url=url, title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None,\n                    published_date=None, category=None, source=\"fake\",\n                    scraped_at=\"now\")\n\n\nclass TestCrawl:\n    def test_skips_already_seen_urls(self, isolated_dirs):\n        src = FakeSource([\"a\", \"b\"], {\"a\": make_article(\"a\"), \"b\": make_article(\"b\")})\n        src._save_state({\"seen_urls\": [\"a\"], \"total_saved\": 1})\n        saved = src.crawl(limit=10)\n        assert [a.url for a in saved] == [\"b\"]\n\n    def test_per_article_exception_is_skipped_not_fatal(self, isolated_dirs):\n        src = FakeSource([\"a\", \"b\"], {\"b\": make_article(\"b\")}, fail_urls={\"a\"})\n        saved = src.crawl(limit=10)\n        assert [a.url for a in saved] == [\"b\"]\n\n    def test_non_article_marks_seen_without_incrementing_total(self, isolated_dirs):\n        src = FakeSource([\"a\"], {\"a\": None})  # parse_article returns None\n        src.crawl(limit=10)\n        state = src._load_state()\n        assert \"a\" in state[\"seen_urls\"]\n        assert state.get(\"total_saved\", 0) == 0\n\n    def test_limit_zero_is_unlimited(self, isolated_dirs):\n        urls = [f\"u{i}\" for i in range(5)]\n        src = FakeSource(urls, {u: make_article(u) for u in urls})\n        saved = src.crawl(limit=0)\n        assert len(saved) == 5\n\n    def test_limit_reached_sets_stopped_reason(self, isolated_dirs):\n        urls = [f\"u{i}\" for i in range(5)]\n        src = FakeSource(urls, {u: make_article(u) for u in urls})\n        src.crawl(limit=2)\n        assert src._load_state()[\"last_stopped_reason\"] == \"limit reached\"\n\n    def test_exhausted_sets_stopped_reason(self, isolated_dirs):\n        src = FakeSource([], {})\n        src.crawl(limit=10)\n        assert src._load_state()[\"last_stopped_reason\"] == \"exhausted\"\n\n    def test_discovery_error_is_caught_not_raised(self, isolated_dirs):\n        src = FakeSource([], discovery_error=ConnectionError(\"network down\"))\n        saved = src.crawl(limit=10)  # must not raise\n        assert saved == []\n        assert \"error\" in src._load_state()[\"last_stopped_reason\"]\n\n    def test_on_save_called_only_for_saved_articles(self, isolated_dirs):\n        calls = []\n        src = FakeSource([\"a\", \"b\"], {\"a\": make_article(\"a\"), \"b\": None})\n        src.crawl(limit=10, on_save=calls.append)\n        assert [a.url for a in calls] == [\"a\"]\n\n\nclass TestParseArticle:\n    def test_missing_title_returns_none(self, isolated_dirs):\n        ...  # mock self.fetch() page.css(title).first -> None\n\n    def test_embed_url_skips_about_blank_iframe_falls_back_to_video(self, isolated_dirs):\n        ...\n\n    def test_published_date_attr_vs_formatted_text_branches(self, isolated_dirs):\n        ...\n\n\nclass TestExtractImages:\n    def test_dedupes_cover_and_body_images(self):\n        ...\n\n    def test_prefers_data_src_over_src(self):\n        ...\n\n    def test_skips_data_uri_images(self):\n        ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `providers.py` — custom crawl logic (highest-risk, currently 0% covered)\n\nThese three providers hand-roll discovery instead of using the generic sitemap walker — that's where the real logic (and bugs) live.\n\n| Class/method | Gaps |\n|---|---|\n| `MadagascarTribune._is_article_link` | boundary cases: `\"foo-.html\"` rejected, `\"http://x.html\"` rejected, `\"/x.html\"` rejected, `\"_Name,id_.html\"` rejected, plain `\"foo.html\"` accepted |\n| `MadagascarTribune._discover_categories` | homepage fetch failure → `[]` (not raise) |\n| `MadagascarTribune.list_article_urls` | pagination stops when `new_on_page == 0`; respects `_max_pages_per_category` cap; per-category fetch failure breaks only that category, not the whole crawl; canonical redirect URL (`page.url`) used for subsequent pagination |\n| `FreeNews.list_article_urls` | `HTTPError(400)` → stops cleanly (past last page); other `HTTPError` codes → re-raised; empty `posts` list → stops; pagination increments correctly |\n| `Moov.list_article_urls` | BFS dedup via `queued` set (no revisits); yields URL *before* attempting frontier expansion (so a fetch failure during expansion doesn't lose the already-yielded URL); frontier-expansion fetch failure is swallowed, not fatal |\n| `PROVIDERS` dict | each entry's `source_name` matches its dict key (currently unchecked — a typo here silently breaks `main.py`'s `--provider` lookup) |\n\n```python\n# tests/test_providers.py\nimport urllib.error\nimport pytest\nfrom providers import MadagascarTribune, FreeNews, Moov, PROVIDERS\n\n\nclass TestTribuneIsArticleLink:\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"href,expected\", [\n        (\"some-article.html\", True),\n        (\"category-.html\", False),          # rubrique suffix\n        (\"http://external.com/x.html\", False),\n        (\"/absolute-path.html\", False),\n        (\"_AuthorName,42_.html\", False),\n        (None, False),\n        (\"no-extension\", False),\n    ])\n    def test_is_article_link(self, href, expected):\n        assert MadagascarTribune._is_article_link(href) is expected\n\n\nclass TestTribuneDiscoverCategories:\n    def test_homepage_fetch_failure_returns_empty_list(self, monkeypatch):\n        src = MadagascarTribune()\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"providers.Fetcher.get\", lambda *a, **k: (_ for _ in ()).throw(RuntimeError()))\n        assert src._discover_categories() == []\n\n\nclass TestTribuneListArticleUrls:\n    def test_stops_when_page_has_no_new_links(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...\n\n    def test_respects_max_pages_per_category_cap(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...\n\n    def test_category_fetch_failure_skips_only_that_category(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...\n\n\nclass TestFreeNewsListArticleUrls:\n    def test_stops_on_http_400_past_last_page(self, monkeypatch):\n        def fake_urlopen(req, timeout=20):\n            raise urllib.error.HTTPError(req.full_url, 400, \"bad\", {}, None)\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"urllib.request.urlopen\", fake_urlopen)\n        src = FreeNews()\n        assert list(src.list_article_urls()) == []\n\n    def test_reraises_non_400_http_error(self, monkeypatch):\n        def fake_urlopen(req, timeout=20):\n            raise urllib.error.HTTPError(req.full_url, 500, \"err\", {}, None)\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"urllib.request.urlopen\", fake_urlopen)\n        src = FreeNews()\n        with pytest.raises(urllib.error.HTTPError):\n            list(src.list_article_urls())\n\n    def test_paginates_until_empty_page(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...\n\n\nclass TestMoovListArticleUrls:\n    def test_bfs_does_not_revisit_queued_urls(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...\n\n    def test_frontier_expansion_failure_does_not_stop_crawl(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...\n\n\ndef test_all_provider_source_names_match_dict_keys():\n    for key, cls in PROVIDERS.items():\n        assert cls.source_name == key\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `main.py` — CLI (untested)\n\n```python\n# tests/test_main.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock\nimport main\nfrom providers import PROVIDERS\n\nclass TestMainCli:\n    def test_single_provider_invokes_only_that_source(self, monkeypatch, capsys):\n        fake_source = MagicMock()\n        fake_source.crawl.return_value = []\n        fake_source._data_path = \"d\"\n        fake_source._state_path = \"s\"\n        fake_source._log_path = \"l\"\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"main.py\", \"newsmada\", \"--limit\", \"3\"])\n        monkeypatch.setitem(PROVIDERS, \"newsmada\", lambda: fake_source)\n        main.main()\n        fake_source.crawl.assert_called_once()\n        assert fake_source.crawl.call_args.kwargs[\"limit\"] == 3\n\n    def test_all_invokes_every_provider(self, monkeypatch):\n        ...\n\n    def test_invalid_provider_choice_exits_nonzero(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"main.py\", \"not-a-real-provider\"])\n        with pytest.raises(SystemExit):\n            main.main()\n\n    def test_on_save_callback_prints_progress_line(self, monkeypatch, capsys):\n        ...  # verify the f\"  - {title!r} ({date})\" line is flushed per article\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Integration gaps\n\n1. **Selector regression tests** — none of the 11 providers has a fixture-HTML test asserting its `SiteSelectors` actually extract title/body/author/date/category from a saved sample page. These selectors are the single most fragile part of the system (sites redesign constantly) and are 100% unverified. Recommend one `tests/fixtures/<provider>.html` + one `test_parse_article_extracts_fields` per provider, using `unittest.mock` to swap `fetch()` for a fixture-backed `Fetcher`-like object rather than hitting the network.\n2. **Full `crawl()` round-trip across two runs** — write state/data to a `tmp_path`, run `crawl()` twice, assert the second run only fetches URLs not in `seen_urls` and `total_saved` accumulates correctly.\n3. **Concurrent/interrupted-write safety** — no test that `_save_state`'s tmp-file-then-replace actually leaves a valid file if interrupted (hard to test directly, but can at least assert `.json.tmp` doesn't linger after a successful save).\n4. **Non-ASCII round-trip** — Malagasy/French article bodies with accents through `_append_article` → read back from JSONL and confirm `ensure_ascii=False` didn't corrupt anything.\n\n---\n\n### Priority order\n\n1. `NewsSource.crawl()` state machine (base.py) — highest risk, most complex, zero coverage, drives every provider's resumability guarantee.\n2. `MadagascarTribune`, `FreeNews`, `Moov` custom `list_article_urls()` — hand-written pagination/BFS logic prone to off-by-one and infinite-loop bugs.\n3. Date parsers — cheap to test, catches the unvalidated-calendar-date issue above.\n4. Selector fixture tests per provider — lower urgency for correctness-of-logic but highest value for catching silent breakage when a news site redesigns.\n5. `main.py` CLI — low complexity, quick to cover.\n",
