        "title": "3. `providers.py` — custom crawl logic (highest-risk, currently 0% covered)",
        "content": "\nThese three providers hand-roll discovery instead of using the generic sitemap walker — that's where the real logic (and bugs) live.\n\n| Class/method | Gaps |\n|---|---|\n| `MadagascarTribune._is_article_link` | boundary cases: `\"foo-.html\"` rejected, `\"http://x.html\"` rejected, `\"/x.html\"` rejected, `\"_Name,id_.html\"` rejected, plain `\"foo.html\"` accepted |\n| `MadagascarTribune._discover_categories` | homepage fetch failure → `[]` (not raise) |\n| `MadagascarTribune.list_article_urls` | pagination stops when `new_on_page == 0`; respects `_max_pages_per_category` cap; per-category fetch failure breaks only that category, not the whole crawl; canonical redirect URL (`page.url`) used for subsequent pagination |\n| `FreeNews.list_article_urls` | `HTTPError(400)` → stops cleanly (past last page); other `HTTPError` codes → re-raised; empty `posts` list → stops; pagination increments correctly |\n| `Moov.list_article_urls` | BFS dedup via `queued` set (no revisits); yields URL *before* attempting frontier expansion (so a fetch failure during expansion doesn't lose the already-yielded URL); frontier-expansion fetch failure is swallowed, not fatal |\n| `PROVIDERS` dict | each entry's `source_name` matches its dict key (currently unchecked — a typo here silently breaks `main.py`'s `--provider` lookup) |\n\n```python\n",
